Remarks . The new species can be assigned to the
Amynthas morrisi
species group due to the presence of two pairs of spermathecal pores in 5/6/7 ( Sims & Easton 1972 ). To date, the
A. morrisi
group comprises 47 species, of which 13 species have been recorded in northern and central Vietnam ( Thai 1982 , 1984a , b; Le 1995 ; Pham 1995 ;
Do et al . 1994
, 1995 ;
Nguyen et al. 2016a
).
